15 WHEREAS, dedicated individuals in Oklahoma breed dogs to develop
16 unique predictable characteristics that enable dogs to excel in a
17 wide range of beneficial areas; and
18 WHEREAS, purebred dogs are living legacies of the cultures that
19 created them, and historically, these dogs worked alongside their
20 people and provided them companionship; and
21 WHEREAS, the service of these breeds continues as they work
22 alongside humans and provide inestimable companionship as guide
23 dogs, service dogs, conservation dogs, livestock guardians, search
24 and rescue dogs, earth dogs, police dogs, canine soldiers serving by
